[I] Something between PyTorch and karpathy/micrograd

[T] Despite tinygrad's size, it is a fully featured deep learning framework.
[T] Due to its extreme simplicity, it is the easiest framework to add new
[T] accelerators to, with support for both inference and training. If XLA is
[T] CISC, tinygrad is RISC.

[U] https://tinygrad.org/

[A] tinygrad
